<Content>Comfortable hotel, lousy location I stayed in Hong Kong at this hotel for five nights at the beginning of May 2007. The Novotel is right out of the wrapper. It is a very new hotel located near the airport. This is the major issue. Although it is on a metro line (Tung Chung line), it is the very last stop on the line. You are looking at a healthy walk through the mall to the metro station and then a solid 30+ minutes to make it to Hong Kong central station where all of the action is.The rooms are roomy with a funky modern design. They were quiet with no disturbance from other guests. Room Service was OK. I made the mistake of trying some local delicacies. Ugly American tries native Cantonese cuisine. I should have been smarter.The hotel bar is nice but the servers seem to be in a perpetual hurry.The front desk staff was very pleasant and always helpful.The shuttle service to the airport was a big help because I had to take a day trip to Shanghai. NOTE: When you arrive in HKG, exit the baggage, area and then go to the orange Hotel Shuttle desk on the far right of the big concourse. Tell them you are going to the Novotel Citygate. They will set you up and call the hotel, no charge.In total, I would definitely recommend this hotel for business travelers with appointments focused in Kowloon. However, if you are a tourist, you will want to find something closer. 
