<Content>They forgot our wake up call This was our first stop on a two month around the world trip. This is a beautifully new and stylish hotel. The lobby is stunning and I would stay here again. We did encounter some problems however.We came in from Australia and our family of four had to be up early to catch our flight the next day onto europe and we chose this hotel after the not so positive reviews about the regal airport hotel. Unfortunatly our wake up call never came and we slept through. We had even booked with their shuttle service to take us to the airport and when we didnt show, it still didnt occur to the front desk staff to give our room a call. Sufice to say we would have missed our plane but due to bad weather we ended up having a 10 hour delay anyway. Funnily enough Qantas put us up at the Regal and I was most impressed. Dont be put off by all the other reviews we were very pleased with it. I must admit we did not check in at a busy time though. Being toted as almost an 'airport hotel' because of its location it is imperitive that things like, wake up calls, are reliable. One note to family travellers, at the time novotel had a policy that children under 12 could stay in a room free with parents. This particular hotel didnt want to do this as it was quite restrictive with the extra beds in the room. We did however push the point and they did allow us to have all four in one room for the same price. This was fantastic as we didnt need to pay for two rooms. Being that it was such a short stopover all being in one room wasnt a problem. As mentioned in other review there is also a shopping centre attatched which is great if you want to pick up bits and pieces from the supermarket to take on your travels.If your not sure and trying to decide between the regal and the citygate, Id say the citygate is alot more stylish and has the convenience of shops, etc. It does still take a small taxi ride however to get there. So you need to be extra organized to make sure you get to the airport on time.The regal was still really well presented and I was pleased with the rooms. Its so well placed to the airport you just have to walk your luggage through a covered walkway and theres no need to get money out to pay taxi drivers, etc. 
