<Content>Great airport hotel This hotel is at the Citygate shopping centre in Tung Chung, on Lantau Island, only 5 mins drive from the airport (about $60 HK taxi). There is a free shuttle to the airport every half hour. From our room we could see the Ngong Ping Skyrail which goes up to the Giant Buddha (Tian Tan Buddha) statue. The hotel is upmarket Novotel with the Chinese touch. Reception was efficient but tried to sell us a more expensive package than the one I had booked. Nobody offered to carry our bags upstairs. The upper floors are the 鈥楤iz鈥?floors but all rooms have wired or wi-fi broadband access, as well as plasma TV, mini-bar, etc. The hotel rooms are of very modern design, with open plan washbasin and counter, but personally I didn鈥檛 like the opaque glass toilet and shower cubicles. Apart from the lack of privacy (I prefer a solid door between bathroom and bedroom), the water from the shower cubicle leaked under the glass partition to the floor of the loo. The bed was very comfortable and the lighting hi-tech and centralised 鈥?which meant that you could not go to the loo at night without putting on at least the 鈥榥ight light鈥?and disturbing your partner. The breakfast buffet at $118 HK (拢9 at current rates) was excellent value with a huge range of cereals, fresh fruit, patisserie, bacon, sausages and pancakes, waffles and eggs cooked to order, as well as a range of Chinese dishes including spring rolls and dumplings. The same restaurant (Essence) also does a lunch buffet and dinner buffet ($148 HK) but closes at 9.30pm so we could not try this. Instead we ate in the bar area (Andante) which has light meals, snacks and salads. On level 2, there is a coffee shop (Moccato) for simpler breakfasts and access to 2 floors of outlet shops, such as Esprit, Columbia Sportswear, Giordano, Laura Ashley, etc. offering serious reductions. More shops opening soon! An excellent hotel for early flights but leave some time for bargain-hunting. 
